pulism.'' London: NLB/Atlantic Highlands Humanities Press.\n*{{cite book|authorlink=Zeev Sternhell|last1=Sternhell |first1=Zeev |first2=Mario |last2=Sznajder |first3=Maia |last3=Asheri |year=1994 |title=The Birth of Fascist Ideology, From Cultural Rebellion to Political Revolution |translator-first1=David |translator-last1=Maisei |publisher=Princeton University Press |ref=harv}}\n*Fritzsche, Peter. 1990. ''Rehearsals for Fascism: Populism and Political Mobilization in Weimar Germany''. New York: Oxford University Press. {{ISBN|978-0-19-505780-5}}\n*Gentile, Emilio. 2002. ''Fascismo. Storia ed interpretazione'' . Roma-Bari: Giuseppe Laterza & Figli.\n\n===Bibliography on international fascism===\n*[[Kevin Coogan|Coogan, Kevin]]. 1999. ''Dreamer of the Day: Francis Parker Yockey and the Postwar Fascist International''. Brooklyn, N.Y.: Autonomedia.\n*{{cite book|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=fcn5ZtaPc7oC |last=Griffin |first=Roger |year=1991 |title=The Nature of Fascism |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |isbn=978-0312071325 |ref=harv}}\n*[[Michael Ledeen|Ledeen, Michael]]. 1972. ''Universal Fascism: The Theory and Practice of the Fascist International, 1928-1936''. New York: Fertig.\n*{{cite book|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=qwO2QgAACAAJ |authorlink=Robert Paxton |last=Paxton |first=Robert O |year=2004 |title=The Anatomy of Fascism |publisher=Alfred A. Knopf |isbn=978-1-4000-4094-0 |ref=harv}}\n*[[Eugen Weber|Weber, Eugen]]. [1964] 1982. ''Varieties of Fascism: Doctrines of Revolution in the Twentieth Century,'' New York: Van Nostrand Reinhold Company, (Contains chapters on fascist movements in different countries.)\n\n==Further reading==\n*[[George Seldes|Seldes, George]]. 1935. ''Sawdust Caesar: The Untold History of Mussolini and Fascism''. New York and London: Harper and Brothers.\n*[[Wilhelm Reich|Reich, Wilhelm]]. 1970. ''The Mass Psychology of Fascism''. New York: Farrar, Straus & Giroux.\n*{{cite book|authorlink=Emilio Gentile |last=Gentile |first=Emilo |year=2003 |title=The Struggle for Modernity: Nationalism, Futurism, and Fascism |publisher=Praeger Publishers |isbn=978-0-275-97692-7 |ref=harv}}\n*[[Edwin Black|Black, Edwin]]. 2001. [https://web.archive.org/web/20060528214237/http://www.ibmandtheholocaust.com/home.php ''IBM and the Holocaust: The Strategic Alliance between Nazi Germany and America's Most Powerful Corporation''] Crown. {{ISBN|978-0-609-60799-2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n*[http://www.worldfuturefund.org/wffmaster/Reading/Germany/mussolini.htm The Doctrine of Fascism signed by Benito Mussolini (complete text)]\n*[http://media.wix.com/ugd/927b40_c1ee26114a4d480cb048f5f96a4cc68f.pdf Authorized translation of Mussolini\u2019s \"The Political and Social Doctrine of Fascism\" (1933)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051222175741/http://www.dkrenton.co.uk/research/polecon.htm The Political Economy of Fascism - From Dave Renton's anti-fascist website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050915163028/http://www.wzo.org.il/en/resources/view.asp?id=585 Fascism and Zionism - From The Hagshama Department - World Zionist Organization]\n*[http://www.rationalrevolution.net/articles/understanding_fascism.htm Fascism Part I - Understanding Fascism and Anti-Semitism]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130930081524/http://www.themodernword.com/eco/eco_blackshirt.html Eternal Fascism: Fourteen Ways of Looking at a Blackshirt] - [[Umberto Eco]]'s list of 14 characteristics of Fascism, originally published 1995.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050830130336/http://www.fascismoeliberta.net/ Site of an Italian fascist party] Italian and German languages\n*[http://www.metaxas-project.com/ Site dedicated to the period of fascism in Greece (1936-1941)]\n*Text of the papal encyclical [http://www.papalencyclicals.net/Pius11/P11QUADR.HTM ''Quadragesimo Anno''].\n*[https://historycooperative.org/nazis-america-the-usas-fascist-past/ Profits \u00fcber Alles! American Corporations and Hitler] by Jacques R. Pauwels\n\